epends on the existing institutional arrangements and mechanisms. Of paramount importance is perhaps the need to facilitate the establishment and empowerment of water use associations and apex bodies. In the study area, this appears to be promising enough to build 'strong' institutional platforms through which water and land resources would be managed sustainably. (C) 2007 Elsevier Ltd. All rights reserved.
